subSubSection.paragraph:
Food and Feeding.
The Ipanema Broad-nosed Batis frugivorous and has been recorded consuming fruits of 
Solanum
granulosoleprosum and S. sanctae-catharinae (both 
Solanaceae
); 
Ficus
enormis, EFinsipida, and 
Maclura
tinctoria (all 
Moraceae
); 
Pouteria
caimito (
Sapotaceae
); 
Miconia brasiliensis
(
Melastomataceae
); and 
Eugenia
sp. (
Myrtaceae
) and pulp of 
Citharexylum
solanaceum (
Verbenaceae
). These data suggest that the Ipanema Broadnosed Bat disperse small and large seeds. Pollen grains were found in the stomach of one individual from south-eastern 
Brazil
.
